        "\n",
        "**Concept:** A `for` loop is used for iterating over a sequence (that is, a list, tuple, dictionary, set, string, or range). It executes a block of code for each item in the sequence.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Used In Program:**\n",
        "```python\n",
        "for i in range(3):\n",
        "    print(f\"  Count: {i}\")\n",
        "```\n",
        "- **`range(n)`:** Generates a sequence of numbers from 0 up to (but not including) `n`. `range(3)` produces 0, 1, 2.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Expected Output:** Prints"
