      "source": [
        "### 7. While Loops\n",
        "\n",
        "**Concept:** A `while` loop repeatedly executes a block of code as long as a given condition is `True`. It's essential to include logic within the loop that will eventually make the condition `False` to prevent an infinite loop.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Used In Program:**\n",
        "```python\n",
        "count = 0\n",
        "while count < 3:\n",
        "    print(f\"  While count: {count}\")\n",
        "    count += 1\n",
        "```\n",
        "- **Condition:** `count < 3` is evaluated before each iteration.\n",
        "- **Increment:** `count += 1` changes the value of `count`, eventually making the condition `False`.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Expected Output:** Prints \"  While count: 0\", \"  While count: 1\", \"  While count: 2\".\n",
        "\n",
        "**Alternative Methods/Notes:**\n",
        "- `break` statement: Immediately exits the loop.\n",
        "- `continue` statement: Skips the rest of the current iteration and moves to the next iteration."
      ]
    },
